<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bower1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bower,</orth> subst., an arbour, a shady recess amidst trees and flowers: <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 1, 202</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 1, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.210" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 210</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 92</bibl>. == a pleasant habitation: <cit><quote>sweet beauty hath no name, no holy b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 127.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 127, 7</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>